<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-18T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="723" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/99: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-18T10:00:00+01:00">March 18, 1931—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 18—7:45 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. Department’s telegram No. 9, February 24, 5 p.m. Federal Council
                            approved supplemental article and reservation yesterday. President
                            expected to ratify within a few days. Austrian Government will be
                            prepared to exchange ratifications whenever I have received American
                            instrument of ratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>